verbose_text: In our study, the early wound closure and limited scar tissue formation in the wounds treated with oral mucosal cell sheet might have been mediated by the increased expression of KRT14, VEGFA, IL10, and AQP3 and the relatively low expression of TGFB1, IL6, ICAM1, ACTA2, and FN1 during wound healing.
evidence: scar tissue formation in the wounds treated with oral mucosal cell sheet might have been mediated by the increased expression of KRT14, VEGFA, IL10, and AQP3 and the relatively low expression of TGFB1, IL6, ICAM1, ACTA2
